1
00:00:36,167 --> 00:00:38,800
<i>If Felma and Manuel get back
together with their kids,</i>

2
00:00:38,933 --> 00:00:41,067
<i>you'll lose your place
in his life.</i>

3
00:00:41,200 --> 00:00:44,067
<i>Only our marriage will be
annulled,</i>

4
00:00:44,200 --> 00:00:46,133
<i> not my being your father.</i>

5
00:00:46,267 --> 00:00:48,467
<i> I love you so much, Dad.</i>

6
00:00:48,600 --> 00:00:51,600
<i>What are you doing to stop
your dad from filing the case?</i>

7
00:00:51,733 --> 00:00:53,333
<i> There! Confess to them!</i>

8
00:00:53,467 --> 00:00:54,733
<i>- Jessica!
- Let go of Jessica!</i>

9
00:00:54,867 --> 00:00:56,700
<i>-Jessica, that's enough! Coleen!
-Coleen, come on!</i>

10
00:00:56,833 --> 00:00:58,233
<i>She's talking to her mom again.</i>

11
00:00:58,367 --> 00:00:59,833
<i>Dad, they're planning something.</i>

12
00:00:59,967 --> 00:01:02,900
<i>You just love to assume
and accuse people of things!</i>

13
00:01:06,567 --> 00:01:07,600
<i>- Jessica!
- Coleen, dear!</i>

14
00:01:07,767 --> 00:01:09,300
<i>What is your sister Coleen
talking about?</i>

15
00:01:09,433 --> 00:01:11,867
<i>When Mom found out about
the annulment,</i>

16
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:15,767
<i>She said if it pushes through,
I'm going to live with her.</i>

17
00:01:15,900 --> 00:01:19,133
<i>Mom, did you know about Coleen's
father's annulment?</i>

18
00:01:19,267 --> 00:01:20,100
<i> Yes, Son.</i>

19
00:01:20,233 --> 00:01:21,567
<i> But I'm staying out of it.</i>

20
00:01:21,700 --> 00:01:25,400
<i>Mom, if Dad's annulment
gets granted,</i>

21
00:01:25,533 --> 00:01:26,767
<i> will you get back together?</i>

22
00:01:26,900 --> 00:01:28,667
<i>I was about to invite
Mom for coffee,</i>

23
00:01:28,800 --> 00:01:30,300
<i> but she's not in her room.</i>

24
00:01:30,433 --> 00:01:31,567
<i>What about you?
Why are you still up?</i>

25
00:01:31,700 --> 00:01:33,800
<i> Dad's not in our room either.</i>

26
00:01:33,933 --> 00:01:35,533
<i> I was looking for him too.</i>

27
00:01:38,300 --> 00:01:40,200
I'm sorry, Felma.

28
00:01:40,333 --> 00:01:41,200
Oh...

29
00:01:41,367 --> 00:01:43,500
It's just hard to say
goodbye to you.

30
00:01:45,533 --> 00:01:46,867
You know, if only we could...

31
00:01:47,900 --> 00:01:50,367
If only we really could,
we wouldn't leave at all.

32
00:01:50,500 --> 00:01:52,700
You have to, Manuel.

33
00:01:52,833 --> 00:01:55,867
So people stop questioning
what's going on between us.

34
00:01:57,500 --> 00:02:00,033
Fix what needs
to be fixed first.

35
00:02:01,633 --> 00:02:03,300
Then you can come back.

36
00:02:05,367 --> 00:02:07,167
Wait for me, Felma.

37
00:02:08,533 --> 00:02:09,567
Please, wait for me.

38
00:02:25,833 --> 00:02:26,933
Coleen?

39
00:02:32,233 --> 00:02:34,033
What are you doing here?

40
00:02:34,167 --> 00:02:36,200
Were you listening
to our conversation?

41
00:02:41,167 --> 00:02:42,133
What?

42
00:02:42,267 --> 00:02:44,100
Mom, Dad, stop!

43
00:02:44,233 --> 00:02:46,267
My stomach hurts
from laughing so much!

44
00:02:50,467 --> 00:02:51,600
What's going on here?

45
00:02:51,733 --> 00:02:53,533
Oh, Jeffrey.

46
00:02:53,667 --> 00:02:56,233
Oh, Isn't it obvious?

47
00:02:56,367 --> 00:02:58,733
We're having a good laugh.

48
00:02:59,967 --> 00:03:02,233
Having a good laugh
but why only you laughing?

49
00:03:02,367 --> 00:03:03,500
No, Jeffrey.

50
00:03:03,633 --> 00:03:06,167
I told them a joke,
but they didn't get it.

51
00:03:06,300 --> 00:03:07,833
Maybe you will, Jeffrey.

52
00:03:07,967 --> 00:03:09,400
Wanna hear it?

53
00:03:09,533 --> 00:03:10,600
What are you doing here, Mom?

54
00:03:10,733 --> 00:03:12,367
Why are you hanging out alone
with your ex?

55
00:03:12,500 --> 00:03:14,467
Jeff, no! It's not like that.

56
00:03:14,600 --> 00:03:17,667
I just asked them
for love advice.

57
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:20,433
There's this guy at school
who's courting me.

58
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:22,567
And I kinda like him too.

59
00:03:22,700 --> 00:03:24,500
But there's a catch.

60
00:03:24,633 --> 00:03:27,233
They say he's also courting
someone from another department.

61
00:03:29,033 --> 00:03:31,200
And you went to them for advice?

62
00:03:31,333 --> 00:03:32,500
He's courting someone else?

63
00:03:32,633 --> 00:03:34,067
Coleen, come on,
It's obvious.

64
00:03:34,200 --> 00:03:35,700
That's a huge
red flag right there.

65
00:03:36,833 --> 00:03:38,667
He's already acting shady, and
you're not even together yet?

66
00:03:38,800 --> 00:03:40,433
What more if you do
end up together,

67
00:03:40,567 --> 00:03:42,633
get married, and start a family?

68
00:03:42,767 --> 00:03:43,867
Wow, Jeff.

69
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:45,733
Jumping ahead a bit, aren't we?

70
00:03:45,867 --> 00:03:47,400
Marriage and kids already?

71
00:03:47,533 --> 00:03:50,633
I'm just saying,
I know guys like that.

72
00:03:50,767 --> 00:03:52,433
Those types?
They're jerks.

73
00:03:52,567 --> 00:03:55,067
Mark my words, give it time,
and he'll cheat,

74
00:03:55,233 --> 00:03:56,467
get some girl pregnant,

75
00:03:56,600 --> 00:03:58,267
then leave his own
family behind.

76
00:03:58,400 --> 00:03:59,367
Look.

77
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:02,167
Oh, Dad, let's go?

78
00:04:03,467 --> 00:04:05,067
Good night, Auntie Felma.

79
00:04:06,100 --> 00:04:07,367
Good night, Jessica.

80
00:04:07,500 --> 00:04:09,700
Coleen, stay here.

81
00:04:09,833 --> 00:04:12,567
Let's talk about your problem.

82
00:04:26,200 --> 00:04:27,867
This kid.

83
00:04:28,033 --> 00:04:28,700
- I've been texting her nonstop,
- Hey, friend.

84
00:04:28,833 --> 00:04:29,800
and still nothing.

85
00:04:29,933 --> 00:04:32,533
You've been holding your phone
for a while now.

86
00:04:32,667 --> 00:04:33,567
I know.

87
00:04:33,700 --> 00:04:34,733
It's Jessica.

88
00:04:34,867 --> 00:04:37,133
I'ven been messaging her,
but she hasn't reply once.

89
00:04:37,267 --> 00:04:39,167
No calls, no texts,
nothing.

90
00:04:39,300 --> 00:04:41,300
I have a bad feeling
about that girl.

91
00:04:41,433 --> 00:04:42,633
Save it for later.

92
00:04:42,767 --> 00:04:44,967
Someone might rat you out
for being on your phone

93
00:04:45,100 --> 00:04:46,467
while on duty.

94
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:47,367
Come on,

95
00:04:47,500 --> 00:04:49,300
this is a family emergency.

96
00:04:49,433 --> 00:04:51,967
They'll understand.

97
00:04:52,100 --> 00:04:53,600
Wait.

98
00:04:57,300 --> 00:04:58,200
What is that?

99
00:04:58,333 --> 00:04:59,567
Still not answering.

100
00:04:59,700 --> 00:05:00,833
Should I just go check on her?

101
00:05:01,900 --> 00:05:05,033
What? Do you want to get
suspended again?

102
00:05:05,167 --> 00:05:06,567
You're leaving your post?

103
00:05:06,700 --> 00:05:08,867
Do you want to lose
your job again?

104
00:05:09,900 --> 00:05:12,233
I need to know what's happening
to my daughter.

105
00:05:12,367 --> 00:05:14,100
I need her.

106
00:05:14,233 --> 00:05:15,133
So what now?

107
00:05:15,267 --> 00:05:17,433
You're going to tell her
to stop Manuel again?

108
00:05:17,567 --> 00:05:18,633
Yes.

109
00:05:18,767 --> 00:05:20,500
And on top of that...

110
00:05:20,633 --> 00:05:22,867
I need to scare Jessica

111
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:25,167
into doing what I want.

112
00:05:25,300 --> 00:05:26,900
I need her.

113
00:05:27,033 --> 00:05:29,067
I need her to be on my side.

114
00:05:29,200 --> 00:05:33,167
Who knows?
Manuel might use her against me.

115
00:05:33,300 --> 00:05:35,300
What do you mean?

116
00:05:35,467 --> 00:05:37,133
Atty. Salazar said,

117
00:05:37,267 --> 00:05:40,633
that Jessica could testify
against me

118
00:05:40,767 --> 00:05:42,133
to prove what Manuel
is claiming.

119
00:05:42,267 --> 00:05:44,867
That I'm psychologically
incapacitated.

120
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:46,267
Oh my god.

121
00:05:46,400 --> 00:05:47,400
If that's the case,

122
00:05:47,533 --> 00:05:49,200
you really have to work
double time on Jessica.

123
00:05:49,333 --> 00:05:50,500
Exactly.

124
00:05:50,633 --> 00:05:53,100
But how can I do that
if I can't even contact her?

125
00:05:59,900 --> 00:06:01,233
You're welcome.

126
00:06:01,367 --> 00:06:05,133
Because if I hadn't seen
Jeffrey and Jessica then...

127
00:06:05,267 --> 00:06:06,733
you would have been
caught by now.

128
00:06:08,733 --> 00:06:11,233
What would they have caught?

129
00:06:11,367 --> 00:06:14,000
There's nothing going on
between me and your dad, okay?

130
00:06:14,133 --> 00:06:16,500
Stop reading too much into it.

131
00:06:16,633 --> 00:06:17,700
Sorry.

132
00:06:18,867 --> 00:06:21,300
Are you sure
there's nothing, Mom?

133
00:06:21,433 --> 00:06:23,133
Yes, really.

134
00:06:23,267 --> 00:06:26,867
I can look Jeffrey
and Jessica in the eye.

135
00:06:27,867 --> 00:06:28,933
And even you...

136
00:06:29,067 --> 00:06:30,500
and Andrea.

137
00:06:31,733 --> 00:06:35,467
I can look anyone in the eye
because my conscience is clear.

138
00:06:35,600 --> 00:06:38,767
I thought...

139
00:06:38,900 --> 00:06:41,367
But honestly, Mom,

140
00:06:41,533 --> 00:06:44,433
I'm still hoping that you
and Dad will get back together.

141
00:06:45,467 --> 00:06:47,233
He's married to Hazel.

142
00:06:49,100 --> 00:06:51,067
You really think...

143
00:06:51,200 --> 00:06:54,067
I'd agree to be
your father's mistress?

144
00:06:55,133 --> 00:06:56,633
I'm sorry, Mom.

145
00:06:57,800 --> 00:06:59,833
I just wanted to ask something.

146
00:06:59,967 --> 00:07:03,000
If his marriage gets annulled,

147
00:07:03,133 --> 00:07:05,867
will you and Dad
get back together?

148
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:09,300
I'm not a child anymore to lie

149
00:07:09,433 --> 00:07:10,967
or pretend I don't feel
anything.

150
00:07:11,967 --> 00:07:14,333
But as long as he's married
to someone else,

151
00:07:14,500 --> 00:07:16,400
we will never be back together.

152
00:07:17,433 --> 00:07:18,367
Yes!

153
00:07:18,500 --> 00:07:20,867
I hope their annulment gets
approved soon,

154
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:23,733
so we can finally
be a family again.

155
00:07:23,867 --> 00:07:27,200
Maybe even this year!

156
00:07:27,333 --> 00:07:28,200
Right, Mom?

157
00:07:28,333 --> 00:07:29,300
That's enough.

158
00:07:29,433 --> 00:07:30,867
Come here.

159
00:07:37,567 --> 00:07:39,733
Dad, this place is beautiful.

160
00:07:39,867 --> 00:07:41,067
Not too big.

161
00:07:41,200 --> 00:07:43,167
but not too small either.

162
00:07:43,300 --> 00:07:44,700
Dad, I think this is perfect.

163
00:07:44,833 --> 00:07:45,800
Thank you, Uncle.

164
00:07:45,933 --> 00:07:47,267
- You're welcome, my godchild.
- Thank you.

165
00:07:47,400 --> 00:07:49,233
This is already semi-furnished.

166
00:07:49,400 --> 00:07:52,167
It already has built-in cabinets
and a water heater.

167
00:07:52,300 --> 00:07:55,300
We can even have a ramp
installed for Sir Manuel,

168
00:07:55,433 --> 00:07:57,967
so he can move around easily,
It's very spacious anyway.

169
00:07:58,100 --> 00:07:59,200
Thank you.

170
00:07:59,333 --> 00:08:01,167
This is a prime location.

171
00:08:01,300 --> 00:08:03,700
Near the hospital,
the police station

172
00:08:03,833 --> 00:08:07,067
the church, and lots
of convenience stores nearby.

173
00:08:07,200 --> 00:08:08,667
Very accessible.

174
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:12,000
Dad, this is way better
than the one I found.

175
00:08:12,133 --> 00:08:14,533
I told you, bro,
you'd like this.

176
00:08:14,667 --> 00:08:18,400
Well, if it's okay with you,
then it's okay with me too.

177
00:08:18,533 --> 00:08:20,167
So, Ma'am? Shall we close
the deal?

178
00:08:20,300 --> 00:08:21,533
All right. If it's okay
with you all,

179
00:08:21,700 --> 00:08:23,067
let's go and close the contract.

180
00:08:23,200 --> 00:08:24,833
All right, let's close the deal.

181
00:08:24,967 --> 00:08:26,367
So...

182
00:08:26,500 --> 00:08:28,600
is this our new home?

183
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:37,133
I like it.

184
00:08:37,267 --> 00:08:39,200
It's nice. Cozy.

185
00:08:40,233 --> 00:08:41,667
So, when do we move in?

186
00:08:42,700 --> 00:08:44,933
Hazel, what are you doing here?

187
00:08:45,067 --> 00:08:48,533
And how did you even find us?

188
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:58,033
I always find my ways, Manuel.

189
00:08:58,167 --> 00:09:01,000
<i>You'll help me,
or I'll tell your father</i>

190
00:09:01,133 --> 00:09:05,300
<i>the truth that he raised a child
who isn't even his.</i>

191
00:09:43,367 --> 00:09:44,933
Oh, by the way, Ma'am.

192
00:09:45,067 --> 00:09:48,033
I'm Mrs. Hazel Capistrano-Cruz.

193
00:09:48,167 --> 00:09:50,300
I'm the wife.

194
00:09:50,433 --> 00:09:52,500
- And...
- And the other woman...

195
00:09:52,633 --> 00:09:53,533
is the mistress.

196
00:09:53,667 --> 00:09:56,367
- Oh.
- I'm not a mistress.

197
00:09:56,500 --> 00:09:58,300
Hazel, please not now!

198
00:09:58,433 --> 00:09:59,867
- When?
- Tomorrow,

199
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:00,833
the day after tomorrow,

200
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:02,667
next week, next month!

201
00:10:02,800 --> 00:10:06,033
But not now and not here, Hazel,
have some shame!

202
00:10:06,167 --> 00:10:07,633
Why should I be ashamed?

203
00:10:07,767 --> 00:10:09,167
I'm the wife.

204
00:10:10,500 --> 00:10:12,233
And you, Manuel?

205
00:10:12,367 --> 00:10:13,533
Who are you going to keep here?

206
00:10:14,933 --> 00:10:15,967
Your mistress?

207
00:10:17,367 --> 00:10:20,267
What, are you forcing me to file
a concubinage case against you?

208
00:10:20,400 --> 00:10:21,767
Mom!

209
00:10:23,033 --> 00:10:24,967
And you, Felma.

210
00:10:25,100 --> 00:10:27,667
You really can't let go
of my husband, can you?

211
00:10:27,800 --> 00:10:28,867
- Hazel!
- Mom, Mom, Mom!

212
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:31,033
- Mom? Mom Mom?

213
00:10:31,167 --> 00:10:32,233
- Hazel, stop!
- Mom, Mom. Mom!

214
00:10:32,367 --> 00:10:34,000
- I said stop, Hazel!
- hazel!

215
00:10:37,133 --> 00:10:38,233
Manuel?

216
00:10:38,367 --> 00:10:40,300
I'm so done with you!

217
00:10:43,133 --> 00:10:44,033
Hazel, come here!

218
00:10:47,367 --> 00:10:49,367
I'm sorry, Ma'am,
I'm really sorry.

219
00:10:49,500 --> 00:10:51,367
Why are you apologizing?
Are you embarrassed?

220
00:10:51,500 --> 00:10:53,333
Aren't you a mistress?
You should be shameless!

221
00:10:53,467 --> 00:10:54,400
- Hazel, stop!
- She deserve to be called out

222
00:10:54,533 --> 00:10:55,600
in public, the homewreckers.

223
00:10:55,733 --> 00:10:57,500
- Mom, enough!
- Hazel! Stop!

224
00:10:57,633 --> 00:10:58,933
- Go home now!
- Why would I go home?

225
00:10:59,067 --> 00:11:00,400
I should be the one living here!

226
00:11:00,533 --> 00:11:01,867
- Go home!
- I'm the wife!

227
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:03,700
- Get out of here, Hazel!
- Go home!

228
00:11:05,900 --> 00:11:07,900
- I said leave!
- Come on!

229
00:11:08,067 --> 00:11:09,233
Jessica, stay here.

230
00:11:15,067 --> 00:11:16,567
Go home!

231
00:11:16,700 --> 00:11:18,200
I'm the wife!
Why should I go?

232
00:11:18,333 --> 00:11:20,033
- You're making a scene here!
- Let go of my friend!

233
00:11:20,167 --> 00:11:21,200
- Just go home!
- Let me go!

234
00:11:21,333 --> 00:11:23,567
- You tolerate Manuel.
- Abel, let me go!

235
00:11:23,700 --> 00:11:24,733
- Go home!
- Abel, what are you doing?

236
00:11:24,867 --> 00:11:26,233
You're hurting me!

237
00:11:26,367 --> 00:11:28,500
You have no respect
for women, Abel!

238
00:11:28,633 --> 00:11:31,500
You have no respect for men
or for other women!

239
00:11:31,633 --> 00:11:32,500
You're unbelievable!

240
00:11:32,633 --> 00:11:36,267
Did you leave your shame
in Canada?

241
00:11:36,400 --> 00:11:37,167
- What did you say?
- What? What?

242
00:11:37,300 --> 00:11:38,767
That hurts!

243
00:11:38,900 --> 00:11:40,700
There! You deserve it!

244
00:11:40,833 --> 00:11:41,600
Serves you right!

245
00:11:41,767 --> 00:11:43,300
Ouch!

246
00:11:44,500 --> 00:11:46,967
You're really siding
with her over me?

247
00:11:47,100 --> 00:11:48,467
I'm your mother.

248
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:50,700
You should be on my side!

249
00:11:50,833 --> 00:11:52,500
Mom, when are you going to stop?

250
00:11:52,633 --> 00:11:53,667
Never!

251
00:11:53,800 --> 00:11:55,900
Not until I get you
and your father back!

252
00:11:56,033 --> 00:11:58,100
So help me,
if you want me to stop.

253
00:11:58,233 --> 00:11:58,933
No, Mom.

254
00:11:59,067 --> 00:12:00,967
I will never help you.

255
00:12:01,100 --> 00:12:02,333
Is that so?

256
00:12:02,467 --> 00:12:07,267
Maybe it's time your father
knows the truth.

257
00:12:08,133 --> 00:12:09,267
Mom, no, please.

258
00:12:10,300 --> 00:12:11,900
What truth, Hazel?

259
00:12:12,933 --> 00:12:14,833
Mom, no. No, no.

260
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:16,167
Mom, no, please!

261
00:12:16,300 --> 00:12:18,967
- Mom!
- Abel! Abel!

262
00:12:19,100 --> 00:12:20,300
What are you doing?

263
00:12:20,433 --> 00:12:21,367
Move over.

264
00:12:21,500 --> 00:12:22,700
Stay out of it!

265
00:12:22,833 --> 00:12:23,700
You're just as indulgent
as Hazel!

266
00:12:23,833 --> 00:12:26,167
You both have the same attitude!

267
00:12:26,300 --> 00:12:28,933
I'm really sorry
for what happened.

268
00:12:29,067 --> 00:12:30,700
I'm sorry, too, but...

269
00:12:30,833 --> 00:12:32,400
I'm sorry.

270
00:12:32,533 --> 00:12:34,800
I'm not renting my apartment
to you anymore.

271
00:12:37,533 --> 00:12:39,633
Mom, please,
I'm begging you.

272
00:12:39,767 --> 00:12:41,233
Please, Mom.

273
00:12:41,367 --> 00:12:42,733
I also begged to you, Jessica.

274
00:12:42,867 --> 00:12:44,333
You didn't listen to me.

275
00:12:44,467 --> 00:12:46,100
If you don't want your father
to know the truth,

276
00:12:46,233 --> 00:12:49,300
then you'll come with me,
so he'll follow us.

277
00:12:49,467 --> 00:12:50,667
Mom, please.

278
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:52,267
Have mercy on me and Dad.

279
00:12:52,400 --> 00:12:54,233
Please, Mom.

280
00:12:54,367 --> 00:12:55,833
Did you ever have mercy on me?

281
00:12:55,967 --> 00:12:57,500
No.

282
00:12:57,633 --> 00:13:00,400
So if you won't help me
get your father back,

283
00:13:00,533 --> 00:13:03,133
then I'll take you away
from him.

284
00:13:04,167 --> 00:13:05,267
You're mine.

285
00:13:05,400 --> 00:13:07,167
You're my daughter.

286
00:13:07,300 --> 00:13:09,133
I want them...

287
00:13:09,267 --> 00:13:10,733
to reject you.

288
00:13:11,767 --> 00:13:14,767
I want you to feel what I felt

289
00:13:14,900 --> 00:13:16,433
when my loved ones abandoned me.

290
00:13:17,900 --> 00:13:19,467
Thank you so much,

291
00:13:19,600 --> 00:13:21,533
and I'm sorry for all
the trouble we've caused.

292
00:13:25,067 --> 00:13:27,233
What is it this time, Hazel?

293
00:13:27,367 --> 00:13:28,400
Manuel...

294
00:13:29,533 --> 00:13:30,500
there's something
you need to know,

295
00:13:30,633 --> 00:13:32,400
Mom! No!

296
00:13:33,667 --> 00:13:36,300
Mom, no. Please.

297
00:13:41,100 --> 00:13:43,000
I want you to know
that Jessica...

298
00:13:43,133 --> 00:13:44,700
No, please!
Let me tell him.

299
00:13:44,833 --> 00:13:45,867
Please, Mom.

300
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:48,100
Let me tell him.

301
00:13:48,233 --> 00:13:49,467
What is it that you're going
to tell me?

302
00:13:51,500 --> 00:13:52,833
What is it, Jessica?

303
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:58,567
Dad, I've decided.

304
00:14:01,800 --> 00:14:04,500
I'll stay with Mom for now.

305
00:14:05,967 --> 00:14:07,100
Wait.

306
00:14:07,233 --> 00:14:09,533
Dear, why is it so sudden?

307
00:14:11,433 --> 00:14:12,733
What happened?

308
00:14:12,867 --> 00:14:15,100
What did your mom tell you?
Did she threaten you?

309
00:14:15,233 --> 00:14:17,200
Hey, I didn't do that.

310
00:14:17,333 --> 00:14:21,233
Jessica, if you're being forced
or scared,

311
00:14:21,367 --> 00:14:22,967
just tell your dad.

312
00:14:23,100 --> 00:14:24,800
Stop! Stay out of this!

313
00:14:24,933 --> 00:14:25,733
Stop!

314
00:14:25,867 --> 00:14:26,867
Mom, please.

315
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:29,633
Mom, stop! Everybody stop!

316
00:14:31,467 --> 00:14:36,133
I just want to spend time with
the both of you and Mommy, Dad.

317
00:14:37,300 --> 00:14:39,567
I thought I would just split,

318
00:14:39,700 --> 00:14:40,733
there would be days,

319
00:14:40,867 --> 00:14:42,867
with Mommy and days with you,
Dad.

320
00:14:43,900 --> 00:14:45,100
Dear.

321
00:14:46,767 --> 00:14:49,433
I don't want more fights, Dad.

322
00:14:49,567 --> 00:14:52,133
I don't want more pain po.

323
00:14:55,300 --> 00:15:02,900
We're leaving now

324
00:15:07,333 --> 00:15:13,800
Mom, let's go.

325
00:15:27,800 --> 00:15:30,067
I don't understand, Felma.

326
00:15:30,200 --> 00:15:32,900
I don't understand why Jessica
made such a decision.

327
00:15:35,300 --> 00:15:37,467
Hazel did something.

328
00:15:37,600 --> 00:15:39,433
I can feel it.

329
00:15:39,567 --> 00:15:41,167
She did something to Jessica.

330
00:15:56,100 --> 00:15:57,367
I need to go to sleep now.

331
00:15:57,500 --> 00:15:58,833
I still have work later.

332
00:15:58,967 --> 00:16:01,033
Come here,
sleep beside me.

333
00:16:01,933 --> 00:16:04,133
You were seriously
going to tell Dad?

334
00:16:11,033 --> 00:16:12,433
Yes.

335
00:16:12,567 --> 00:16:14,700
Dead serious.

336
00:16:14,833 --> 00:16:16,967
Because of you.

337
00:16:17,100 --> 00:16:18,933
You forced me to do that.

338
00:16:20,500 --> 00:16:21,900
What now, Mom?

339
00:16:22,967 --> 00:16:24,467
What do you want?

340
00:16:29,333 --> 00:16:31,233
I still want the same, dear.

341
00:16:32,667 --> 00:16:34,567
I want you to do everything.

342
00:16:35,767 --> 00:16:37,133
Everything you can

343
00:16:38,300 --> 00:16:40,600
to stop the annulment.

344
00:16:42,200 --> 00:16:44,433
I want to make it up
to your dad.

345
00:16:45,367 --> 00:16:46,867
For all the times...

346
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:50,100
I failed to show the love...

347
00:16:50,233 --> 00:16:52,300
he deserved from me.

348
00:16:55,200 --> 00:16:57,433
He tried to love you, Mom.

349
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:01,100
But you didn't help him.

350
00:17:02,167 --> 00:17:08,067
Instead of making him fall
for you, you pushed him away.

351
00:17:09,567 --> 00:17:10,867
I know.

352
00:17:12,567 --> 00:17:14,533
I know I failed.

353
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:18,433
But can you blame me

354
00:17:18,567 --> 00:17:20,200
for realizing just now...

355
00:17:21,633 --> 00:17:23,667
that I love your father?

356
00:17:25,633 --> 00:17:26,933
We're the same.

357
00:17:27,967 --> 00:17:30,467
We both didn't love
each other before.

358
00:17:31,733 --> 00:17:35,533
Because back then, the one
I loved was your real father.

359
00:17:37,767 --> 00:17:39,733
But...

360
00:17:39,867 --> 00:17:42,233
look at me.

361
00:17:43,933 --> 00:17:46,167
I love your dad so much now.

362
00:17:48,900 --> 00:17:52,033
So, Jessica, please.

363
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:55,733
Dear, help me.

364
00:17:56,767 --> 00:18:01,800
You will help me,
whether you like it or not.

365
00:18:03,233 --> 00:18:04,567
Because if you don't,

366
00:18:07,433 --> 00:18:10,467
I will proceed with the case
against your father.

367
00:18:10,600 --> 00:18:15,333
If I have to fabricate
evidence, I'll do it.

368
00:18:16,933 --> 00:18:20,000
And you will testify
in my favor.

369
00:18:21,100 --> 00:18:24,400
I'd rather see
your father in prison.

370
00:18:25,467 --> 00:18:28,000
Because neither Felma...

371
00:18:28,133 --> 00:18:29,433
nor I...

372
00:18:30,600 --> 00:18:32,733
and certainly not you...

373
00:18:32,867 --> 00:18:35,067
deserve anything from him.

374
00:18:57,767 --> 00:18:59,333
Hi, Sonny!

375
00:19:07,800 --> 00:19:08,633
I know.

376
00:19:08,767 --> 00:19:10,500
Oh, same here.

377
00:19:10,633 --> 00:19:12,733
I haven't been able to reach
Elvie either.

378
00:19:12,867 --> 00:19:15,300
Actually, it's been
a few days now.

379
00:19:15,433 --> 00:19:19,000
She's probably vacationing
in some other country again.

380
00:19:19,133 --> 00:19:21,400
I'll update you tomorrow, okay?

381
00:19:22,467 --> 00:19:24,967
All right, bye.

382
00:19:29,667 --> 00:19:33,067
Who's Sonny?

383
00:19:33,200 --> 00:19:34,800
A college classmate.

384
00:19:34,933 --> 00:19:38,633
One of the people
I recruited to invest

385
00:19:38,767 --> 00:19:40,467
in Elvie's lending company.

386
00:19:53,167 --> 00:19:54,967
Pick up the call
of your sibling.

387
00:19:55,100 --> 00:19:56,767
It might be an emergency.

388
00:19:56,900 --> 00:19:58,000
I don't care.

389
00:19:59,033 --> 00:20:01,700
I'm standing by what I said
to her.

390
00:20:01,867 --> 00:20:02,700
Oh, right?

391
00:20:02,833 --> 00:20:03,933
So now she's with her dad.

392
00:20:04,067 --> 00:20:05,067
Now, she doesn't have
a sister anymore.

393
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:08,000
Wow, you're really taking
things that far?

394
00:20:08,133 --> 00:20:10,100
Cutting off?

395
00:20:10,233 --> 00:20:11,667
Yes.

396
00:20:11,800 --> 00:20:15,267
Even if you're my best friend,
if you're gonna fight with me,

397
00:20:16,133 --> 00:20:17,300
then that's it, cut off.

398
00:20:19,067 --> 00:20:20,633
<i> Andrea, please answer.</i>

399
00:20:20,767 --> 00:20:22,233
<i> Jeff's back.</i>

400
00:20:22,967 --> 00:20:24,733
<i> Daisy left him.</i>

401
00:20:24,867 --> 00:20:26,633
<i> She took Tetay with her.</i>

402
00:20:26,767 --> 00:20:29,700
<i>Jeff said he's okay,
but he's not.</i>

403
00:20:29,833 --> 00:20:31,900
<i>He's getting drunk every night.</i>

404
00:20:32,033 --> 00:20:33,900
<i> I'm worried.</i>

405
00:20:41,833 --> 00:20:43,233
Read the text message.

406
00:20:43,833 --> 00:20:44,933
Just the text message.

407
00:20:45,067 --> 00:20:46,200
Then read it!

408
00:20:50,267 --> 00:20:52,200
Andrea, please answer.

409
00:20:52,333 --> 00:20:53,500
Jeff's back.

410
00:20:53,633 --> 00:20:54,967
Daisy left him.

411
00:20:55,100 --> 00:20:56,467
She took Tetay with her.

412
00:20:56,600 --> 00:20:58,667
Jeff said he's okay
but he's not.

413
00:20:58,800 --> 00:21:00,733
He's getting drunk every night.

414
00:21:00,867 --> 00:21:01,800
I'm worried...

415
00:21:03,267 --> 00:21:05,333
Jeff went back home?

416
00:21:06,233 --> 00:21:07,833
Our agreement was that
no one goes home

417
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:09,900
until Mom's ex is gone!

418
00:21:12,533 --> 00:21:13,733
Come on, come with me.

419
00:21:14,633 --> 00:21:15,367
Where to?

420
00:21:15,500 --> 00:21:16,667
To Jeff's.

421
00:21:16,800 --> 00:21:19,000
You can't ignore them, right?

422
00:21:19,133 --> 00:21:20,100
Let's go.

423
00:21:23,100 --> 00:21:24,600
He's at our house.

424
00:21:25,300 --> 00:21:27,367
I don't want to see
those people there.

425
00:21:38,400 --> 00:21:39,467
Hello?

426
00:21:40,567 --> 00:21:41,333
Darn you, Daisy.

427
00:21:41,500 --> 00:21:42,900
Why aren't you answering?

428
00:21:46,033 --> 00:21:48,200
I can't even reach my daughter.

429
00:21:49,533 --> 00:21:51,400
You're blocking my call?

430
00:22:01,600 --> 00:22:03,100
Son...

431
00:22:03,233 --> 00:22:04,533
come on, let's have a drink.

432
00:22:13,833 --> 00:22:16,000
Have a drink?

433
00:22:16,167 --> 00:22:17,300
Us?

434
00:22:19,567 --> 00:22:21,800
Are we going to pretend
we're okay?

435
00:22:22,833 --> 00:22:24,333
- Oh...
- Like we're just buddies?

436
00:22:24,467 --> 00:22:27,967
Like a normal father and son?

437
00:22:28,800 --> 00:22:29,967
Okay.

438
00:22:31,333 --> 00:22:33,433
If that's what you want,
then let's pretend.

439
00:22:33,567 --> 00:22:35,133
So even for one night,
you won't fight with me,

440
00:22:35,267 --> 00:22:36,500
and you won't avoid me.

441
00:22:42,167 --> 00:22:43,933
Do you need someone to talk to?

442
00:22:45,433 --> 00:22:46,633
I'm here.

443
00:22:48,233 --> 00:22:50,433
I understand
what you're going through.

444
00:22:52,133 --> 00:22:54,367
I know how it feels
to lose a family.

445
00:22:55,767 --> 00:22:57,600
You're joking, aren't you?

446
00:22:59,500 --> 00:23:00,700
We're not the same.

447
00:23:03,500 --> 00:23:07,900
My family abandoned me.

448
00:23:09,267 --> 00:23:10,333
You...

449
00:23:11,867 --> 00:23:13,567
You abandoned your family.

450
00:23:13,700 --> 00:23:14,800
That's different.

451
00:23:15,833 --> 00:23:17,200
It's the same.

452
00:23:19,367 --> 00:23:20,367
It's the same, Jeff.

453
00:23:20,500 --> 00:23:22,467
We both lost our families.

454
00:23:25,067 --> 00:23:25,667
So, come on.

455
00:23:26,933 --> 00:23:29,367
Talk to me,
maybe I could help.

456
00:23:33,133 --> 00:23:34,467
Are you trying to be
a father now?

457
00:23:34,600 --> 00:23:35,933
Feeling like you're my dad now?

458
00:23:36,633 --> 00:23:37,633
No.

459
00:23:37,767 --> 00:23:38,900
Don't think of me as your dad.

460
00:23:39,033 --> 00:23:40,900
Let's just talk,
man to man.

461
00:23:44,933 --> 00:23:46,167
Man to man...

462
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:51,333
Are you sure?

463
00:23:51,467 --> 00:23:53,400
You're gonna give me advice?

464
00:23:55,933 --> 00:23:57,800
What do you know about it?

465
00:23:57,933 --> 00:23:59,567
Isn't it you who left us?

466
00:24:01,833 --> 00:24:03,800
You have no right
to give advice.

467
00:24:06,533 --> 00:24:08,800
I know what it feels like

468
00:24:08,933 --> 00:24:11,333
not being able to sleep
at night.

469
00:24:11,467 --> 00:24:13,833
Your mind keeps racing.

470
00:24:13,967 --> 00:24:15,800
You keep asking yourself...

471
00:24:17,033 --> 00:24:19,100
how your family's doing.

472
00:24:20,133 --> 00:24:23,100
I know that feeling,
your eyes are shut,

473
00:24:23,233 --> 00:24:25,467
but your mind is wide awake.

474
00:24:27,133 --> 00:24:28,667
Then you get up.

475
00:24:28,833 --> 00:24:30,833
You look for anything to help
you sleep because,

476
00:24:30,967 --> 00:24:33,833
no matter how many drinks
you have,

477
00:24:33,967 --> 00:24:36,000
sleep just won't come.

478
00:24:37,433 --> 00:24:41,233
I know how painful
that wound is.

479
00:24:41,367 --> 00:24:43,600
Even if you can't see it,

480
00:24:43,733 --> 00:24:47,633
you feel it with your whole
being.

481
00:24:49,967 --> 00:24:51,167
You're an idiot.

482
00:24:54,767 --> 00:24:56,367
You know the pain?

483
00:24:57,533 --> 00:24:59,833
So why did you leave us?

484
00:24:59,967 --> 00:25:01,833
Because I'm an idiot!

485
00:25:03,767 --> 00:25:04,867
I'm an idiot, Jeff!

486
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:06,167
An idiot!

487
00:25:10,467 --> 00:25:12,133
I gave in to temptation.

488
00:25:14,400 --> 00:25:17,700
I made a mistake one night,
just one night,

489
00:25:17,833 --> 00:25:20,467
but I've regretted it for the
rest of my life.

490
00:25:25,633 --> 00:25:28,533
So, if you need help,
I'm here.

491
00:25:30,233 --> 00:25:31,100
Jeff.

492
00:25:31,233 --> 00:25:32,900
Don't touch me,
I don't need you.

493
00:25:33,933 --> 00:25:35,300
- Wait a minute.
- I said don't touch me!

494
00:25:35,467 --> 00:25:36,800
I don't need you!

495
00:25:38,200 --> 00:25:39,967
Why you don't understand that?

496
00:25:40,100 --> 00:25:41,567
Don't you understand that?

497
00:25:41,700 --> 00:25:42,833
Jeff!

498
00:25:42,967 --> 00:25:44,200
Jeff!

499
00:25:45,367 --> 00:25:46,300
Felma!

500
00:25:47,267 --> 00:25:49,000
Felma, help!

501
00:25:49,133 --> 00:25:50,033
It's Jeffrey!

502
00:25:50,167 --> 00:25:51,700
- Manuel?
- Jeff!

503
00:25:51,833 --> 00:25:53,000
Manuel!

504
00:25:53,133 --> 00:25:54,667
Andrea, I don't have any money
left for my medicine.

505
00:25:54,800 --> 00:25:55,967
I'm completely drained.

506
00:25:56,100 --> 00:25:57,033
And you're the one
who recruited me

507
00:25:57,167 --> 00:25:58,033
to that lending company, right?

508
00:25:58,167 --> 00:25:59,600
So give me back my money!

509
00:25:59,733 --> 00:26:00,667
Hold on, Sonny.

510
00:26:00,800 --> 00:26:01,800
We're both waiting here.

511
00:26:01,933 --> 00:26:03,100
I don't have any money either.

512
00:26:03,233 --> 00:26:05,333
It has become a huge problem.

513
00:26:05,467 --> 00:26:07,700
We can't solve it anymore.

514
00:26:07,833 --> 00:26:09,600
What's the issue with Andrea?

515
00:26:09,767 --> 00:26:10,933
We've been scammed, Ma'am.

516
00:26:11,067 --> 00:26:13,233
Oh, no, that's trouble.

517
00:26:13,367 --> 00:26:16,067
Why do you want so badly
to leave with Dad?

518
00:26:16,200 --> 00:26:18,367
If you want to go, go ahead.

519
00:26:18,500 --> 00:26:21,933
But you're not taking
my father with you.

520
00:26:22,067 --> 00:26:24,533
You will never take my father
away from me, Coleen.

521
00:26:24,667 --> 00:26:26,233
I won't allow it.
